1.title: Yo-Kai Are Real!
1.plot: A chance encounter with the supernatural butler Whisper opens fifth-grader Nate's eyes to a whole new world of Yo-kai spirits, including the cheeky cat Jibanyan.

2.title: The Famous One
2.plot: Nate investigates reports of a mysterious creature in the local river, and confronts Tattletell, a Yo-kai who makes people spill embarrassing secrets.

3.title: The Rare One
3.plot: Reports of a "Human-Faced Dog" have Nate's classmates spooked, and a juvenile delinquent Yo-kai called Roughraff inspirits Nate's friend Eddie.

4.title: Yo-kai Medallium
4.plot: Nate meets Hungramps, a Yo-kai triggering hunger pangs outside of a convenience store, and contends with an epidemic of forgetfulness caused by Yo-kai Wazzat. Meanwhile... Manjimutt searches for a new career.

5.title: Yo-kai Illoo
5.plot: A Valentine's Day visit from the mysterious Yo-kai Illoo has Nate fuming, and a visit from a paranormal investigator has Nate fearing for the safety of his Yo-kai friends. Meanwhile... Manjimutt's search for his ideal job continues.

6.title: Yo-kai Blazion
6.plot: A class clean-up day is complicated by a visit from a super-motivational Yo-kai, Nate's dentist is inspirited by Negatibuzz, and Signibble interferes with a sleepover party. Meanwhile... Has Manjimutt found his dream career?

7.title: Here's Komasan
7.plot: Nate makes a new friend in Komasan, a country Yo-kai on his first visit to the city, but struggles when the naysaying Nosirs interfere with his class during a test. Meanwhile... Manjimutt seeks to purify himself through pottery.

8.title: Yo-Kai Fidgephant/Yo-Kai Hidabat
8.plot: Things get desperate at Nate's school when it is visited by Fidgephant, a Yo-kai who makes boys need to use the toilet, and Jibanyan is inspirited by Yo-kai Hidabat. Meanwhile... Manjimutt sets his sights on the biggest dream of all!
